In Java, the multiplication operator can be used to multiply a String by a number.
The result of such an expression
is a new String that corresponds to the given String
repeated the given number of times.

frontmatter.shortDescription: The multiplication operator can repeat a String a number of times
frontmatter.shortCorrection: The multiplication operator does not accept a String and a number
